<div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">
  <h1>🔢 Counter Demo</h1>

  <div style="background-color: #e7f3ff; padding: 30px; border-radius: 8px; text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;">
    <h2 style="font-size: 3em; color: #007bff; margin: 0;"><%= @count %></h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.2em; color: #666;">Current Count</p>
  </div>

  <div style="text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;">
    <%= link_to "➕ Increment Counter", counter_path(count: @count),
        style: "background-color: #28a745; color: white; padding: 15px 25px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em;" %>
  </div>

  <div style="background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <h3>🔍 MVC Flow for this page:</h3>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Route:</strong> <code>get "counter" => "mvc_demo#counter"</code></li>
      <li><strong>Controller:</strong> Gets <code>params[:count]</code>, converts to integer, adds 1</li>
      <li><strong>View:</strong> Displays the incremented <code>@count</code> variable</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; margin: 20px 0;">
    <h4>🎯 Key Learning Points:</h4>
    <ul>
      <li>URL parameters are accessible via <code>params[:parameter_name]</code></li>
      <li>Controller processes the data (increment logic)</li>
      <li>Instance variables (like <code>@count</code>) are passed from controller to view</li>
      <li>Each click creates a new HTTP request → route → controller → view cycle</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Current URL:</strong> <code><%= request.url %></code><br>
    <strong>Count Parameter:</strong> <code><%= params[:count] %></code>
  </p>

  <%= link_to "← Back to Demo Home", root_path,
      style: "background-color: #6c757d; color: white; padding: 10px 20px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px;" %>
</div>